MARCSubfieldLabel: Target audience note (R), Source (NR), Materials specified (NR)
Transformation Notes:
[Manifestation] rdamd:P30137 ["indicator 1 label: " + {$a} + "according to: " + {$b} + ("applies to " + {$3}).
If the first indicator is 8, lable is the same as # - Audience
Notes (Uncategorized):
https://github.com/uwlib-cams/MARC2RDA/issues/198

I do not think it is appropriate to use "has intended audience of manifestation" (unstructured description) because the semantics imply intention (by the publisher or producer), and the example data indicate that the values are cataloguer judgement about the audience, not the intention.--Gordon
My understanding is that entering MARC 521 info into Expression descriptions sets is not feasible.--Theo

Justification for Mapping: Since it is ambiguous whether the property applies to Expression or Manifestation, use the Manifestation property . ; lna 2022-05-17
Assume target audience will not vary between expression and manifestation for Reading Grade Level (ind 1) , so select expression property.
Transformation Notes: Prepend string  Reading grade level:  before contents of $a
Problems with Mapping: Don't see an RDA element or relation that expresses the specificity of the display constant, but add as a prefix needed to make sense of contents of $a
Notes (Uncategorized):
Loss of separation of display constant terminology from value of subfield $a - which mIght be controlled from a particular source but is uncontrolled in MARC.  In a specialized setting these values could support special search limiting.

This line with asterisk indicating "any" for Ind 1 value is  not relevant; all valid conditions are now covered by a separate line and the mappings differ. It might be needed to map data that does not contain a "blank" (#) in the indicator 1 byte; that would not be valid but if it occurs, the default  would  need to be to use ind1=8 mapping - "no indicator constant given"
lna 10/19/2022

Justification for Mapping: There doesn't seem to be a way to reference parts of the description to be able to establish an RDA relationship in the MARC mapping, but we could append the materials specified as a parenthetical phrase to the end of the $a note string.
Transformation Notes: Append the string value of subfield 3 , preceded by the label:  Applies to:    .  In  parentheses, coming after the value of $a  and separated by a space.   Example:  Special audience characteristics:  Tactile learners (Applies to: Puzzles)
Notes (Uncategorized): "Loss" of potential separate reference to a part of an expression (or mainfestation) as an aggregated entity.  But since values are not controlled for this field, probably not possible to do anything else in MARC conversion. ; lna 2022-05-17

Justification for Mapping: Provisionally, using unstructured description, use transformation to append contents of this subfield after $a (and after $3, if it is appended) ; lna 2022-05-17
Transformation Notes: Append the string value of subfield b in parentheses and preceded by 'Assigned by: ' after the value of $a (and $3 if present)
